    "After publishing a history of the city of Ferrara in 1700, he began working on a biography of Ferrara artists, <em>Vite de' pittori e scultori ferraresi</em>, in 1704, based on the popular model of <a href=\"/vasarig\">Giorgio Vasari</a> and more closely <a href=\"/baglioneg\">Giovanni Baglione</a>.": [],
    "However, he was exiled to the Veneto for political reasons in 1711, and on his return in 1713, other works caught his attention.": [],
